# 3p_kick_ban — host. P09 host-controls / kick / ban end-to-end test.
#
# Three-player setup:
#   slot 0 = HostA (this script)
#   slot 1 = ClientB
#   slot 2 = ClientC
#
# Host script timing (networked shot mode advances world.tick only
# during MATCH; the lobby-tick loop is wall-clock, so script ticks
# 0..end run at 60Hz regardless of match phase):
#   t=0..~120  lobby — wait for both clients to connect / handshake
#   t=200      kick ClientB (slot 1). Server-side log "X was kicked",
#              enet_peer_disconnect_later → ClientB receives DISCONNECT
#              and returns to title via the new main.c hook.
#   t=260      ban ClientC (slot 2). Same path + lobby_ban_addr +
#              auto-write to bans.txt.
#   t=320      end. Host should still be alive in slot 0; slots 1+2
#              are empty.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/3p_kick_ban_host
network host 24105
name HostA

at  60 shot t060_lobby_full
at 200 kick 1
at 230 shot t230_after_kick
at 260 ban 2
at 290 shot t290_after_ban
at 320 end
